GOMBE – The Gombe State Police Command has parad­ed a 20-year-old man, Babangida Isa for luring a five-year-old girl and raped her behind a Tsangaya (Almajiri) school in Bajoga town, Funakaye Local Government Area of the state. In a release made available to newsmen in Gombe, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) of the State Command, ASP Mahid Muazu Abubakar, said the suspect was reported by the girl’s father, Yahaya Isa. According to the Police report, “On the 6th of June 2023 at about 5 p.m., one Yahaya Isah, male, of Bajoga came to the Division and reported that Babangida Isa lured his five-year-old daughter, whose name was withheld, be­hind one Almajiri school and raped her.” He said, on receipt of the complaint, the said suspect was arrested where he voluntarily confessed to the crime, adding that both the suspect and the vic­tim were taken to the hospital for a medical examination. The suspect, according to Mahid, would soon be charged to court for prosecution. In another development, the Command said they were able to recover 21 cows rustled by a 30-year-old Sale Kabo of Bandila village, Gulani LGA of who was equally arrested. According to the Police report, “On 6th June 2023, one Jauro Ah­madu, a 75 -year-old man of Shu­wari village via Bajoga Funakaye LGA, reported to the Bajoga Divi­sional Police Headquarters that his 21 cows valued at N7 million had been stolen from his village at night. Mahid said the Divisional Po­lice Officer detailed his personnel who immediately commenced an investigation, after which the sus­pect was arrested in connection with the theft which he allegedly confessed he had committed.